## `site-chrome`

The `site-chrome` component yields a series of nested blocks to give access to the various parts of the site chrome.

See below for sass variables that are available for overwriting before importing the site chrome styles.

### Importing Styles
Import the sass partial.

```sass
// app/styles/app.scss
@import \"nypr-ui/site-chrome\";
```

The following variables are available for overwriting.
"}}
{{code-snippet name="sass-vars.scss"}}

{{md-text text="
When overwriting variables, be sure to set them before the import line.

```sass
$site-chrome-link-color: blue;
$site-chrome-link-hover: blue;
@import \"nypr-ui/site-chrome\";
```

### Basic Usage
"}}

{{code-snippet name="site-chrome.hbs"}}

<div style="transform: translate3d(0,0,0)">
{{! BEGIN-SNIPPET site-chrome }}
{{#site-chrome as |chrome|}}

  {{#chrome.top as |top|}}
    This is on the far left
    {{#top.body as |body|}}
      This is inside a full wrapper
      {{#body.corner as |button|}}
        Inside the corner with a button
        {{#component button}}
          The Button
        {{/component}}
      {{/body.corner}}
    {{/top.body}}
  {{/chrome.top}}

  {{#chrome.nav as |nav|}}
    {{#nav.corner}}
      The upper left corner
    {{/nav.corner}}
    
    {{#nav.links as |links|}}
      {{links.link 'foo'}}
      {{#links.link}}non link item{{/links.link}}
    {{/nav.links}}
    
    {{#nav.footer}}
      footer of the nav
    {{/nav.footer}}
  {{/chrome.nav}}
  
  {{#chrome.body}}
    body area
  {{/chrome.body}}
  
  {{#chrome.footer}}
    <span style="color: white">site footer</span>
  {{/chrome.footer}}
{{/site-chrome}}
{{! END-SNIPPET }}
</div>
